===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|yespon}}, {{m|enm|yepson}}, {{m|enm|ȝespon}}, {{m|enm|ȝespen}}, {{m|enm|ȝispon|t=a measure of volume equivalent to that contained in a person’s hands cupped together}}, probably from {{inh|en|ang|*ġēapsponn}}, {{m|ang|*ġēapspann}}, from {{der|en|ang|*ġēap|t=bent, curved}} + {{m|ang|spann|t=measure of the palm or hand}}, equivalent to {{af|en|gap|span}}. Compare {{cog|fy|gasp|t=buckle, clasp}}, {{cog|nl|gesp|t=buckle, clasp}}, {{cog|gml|gespe|t=the cavity between the hands when held together}}, {{cog|non|gaupn||hollow made by cupped hands}}. {{doublet|en|gowpen}}.
===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# {{lb|en|obsolete|UK|dialect}} Amount that can be held in two hands cupped together.
# {{lb|en|obsolete|UK|dialect}} Two hands cupped together.
